		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Quietust</b> [ Tue Dec 26, 2006 12:37 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Note that Konami could use VRC6 only in europe, but since nobody in japan cares about europe, they just scrammed the USA version and adaptated it to PAL timing (and took 2 years doing so).</div>
<br />
<br />It would have been completely infeasible to use the VRC6 version in Europe, since it would have required either retranslating the Japanese version to English again (and subsequently re-removing all of the VRC6 sound, since the European NES still doesn't support expansion sound), or they would have had to take the MMC5 version and then hack it back to VRC6 and 'fake' all of the IRQ scanline counts (since the VRC6 counts scanlines as exactly 113+2/3 CPU cycles).
<br />
<br />In the end, it was <strong>far</strong> easier for them to just take the USA version, change a few timing values in the game engine, make similar adjustments in the music engine, and make a few cosmetic changes (update the titlescreen, etc.).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


