<br />But Nintendo could've ordered a lot more MMC5s to be made than Konami would've for VRC6, even though MMC5 may have been more complex it could've been the same cost or cheaper because of the quantity.  Also there's all kinds of factors when it comes to making chips, like yield % where some amount of the ones made are unusable.  Could totally wreck the cost (or not).
<br />
